main event: A UFO sighting was reported on October 5, 1955 in Ellensburg, Washington. The observation lasted for four minutes and involved two unknown objects, which were potentially evaluated as possible balloons.
interesting points: The observation lasted for four minutes, providing a substantial amount of time to study the unidentified objects.
There were two objects observed, described as round and football-shaped, transparent, and banded together with a red band.
The sighting was made by a housewife in Ellensburg, Washington, with no mention of other witnesses.
The objects were seen during daylight in clear weather conditions, with no mention of any photographs taken.
The evaluation of the objects as possible balloons suggests a prosaic explanation for the sighting.
sighted object: Two unknown objects potentially resembling balloons
